liputra,  \n29\\. _S_ a _n_ _d_ iliputra from Rathitariputra,  \n30 3. Rathitariputra from Bhalukiputra,\n\np. 226\n\n31\\. Bhalukiputra from Krau _\xc3\xb1_ _k_ ikiputrau,  \n32\\. Krau _\xc3\xb1_ _k_ ikiputrau from Vai _t_ _t_ abhatiputra 1,  \n33\\. Vai _t_ _t_ abhatiputra from Kar _s_ akeyiputra 2,  \n34\\. Kar _s_ akeyiputra from Pra _k_ inayogiputra,  \n35\\. Pra _k_ inayogiputra from Sa _\xc3\xb1_ _g_ iviputra 3,  \n36\\. Sa _\xc3\xb1_ _g_ iviputra from Pra _s_ _\xc3\xb1_ iputra \xc3\x82surivasin,  \n37\\. Pra _s_ _\xc3\xb1_ iputra \xc3\x82surivasin from \xc3\x82suraya _n_ a,  \n38\\. \xc3\x82suraya _n_ a from \xc3\x82suri,  \n39\\. \xc3\x82suri\n\n3\\. from Ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_ avalkya,\n\n40\\. Ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_ avalkya from Uddalaka,  \n41\\. Uddalaka from Aru _n_ a,  \n42\\. Aru _n_ a from Upave _s_ i,  \n43\\. Upave _s_ i from Ku _s_ ri,  \n44\\. Ku _s_ ri from Va _g_ a _s_ ravas,  \n45\\. Va _g_ a _s_ ravas from _G_ ihvavat Vadhyoga,  \n46\\. _G_ ihvavat Vadhyoga from Asita Varshaga _n_ a,  \n47\\. Asita Varshaga _n_ a from Harita Ka _s_ yapa,  \n48\\. Harita Ka _s_ yapa from _S_ ilpa Kasyapa,  \n49\\. _S_ ilpa Kasyapa from Ka _s_ yapa Naidhruvi,  \n50\\. Ka _s_ yapa Naidhruvi from Va _k_ ,  \n51\\. Va _k_ from Ambhi _n_ i,  \n52\\. Ambhi _n_ i from \xc3\x82ditya, the Sun.\n\nAs coming from \xc3\x82ditya, the Sun, these pure 4 Ya _g_ us verses have been\nproclaimed by Yag\xc3\xb1avalkya Va _g_ asaneya.\n\np. 227\n\n4 1. The same as far as Sa\xc3\xb1 _g_ iviputra (No. 36), then\n\n36\\. Sa\xc3\xb1 _g_ iviputra from Ma _n_ _d_ ukayani,  \n37\\. Ma _n_ _d_ ukayani from Ma _n_ _d_ avya,  \n38\\. Ma _n_ _d_ avya from Kautsa,  \n39\\. Kautsa from Mahitthi,  \n40\\. Mahitthi from Vamakakshaya _n_ a,  \n41\\. Vamakakshaya _n_ a from _S_ a _n_ _d_ ilya,  \n42\\. _S_ a _n_ _d_ ilya from Vatsya,  \n43\\. Vatsya from Ku _s_ ri,  \n44\\. Ku _s_ ri from Ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_ ava _k_ as Ra _g_ astambayana,  \n45\\. Ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_ ava _k_ as Ra _g_ astambayana from Tura Kavasheya,  \n46\\. Tura Kavasheya from Pra _g_ apati,  \n47\\. Pra _g_ apati from Brahman,  \n48\\. Brahman is Svayambhu, self-existent.\n\nAdoration to Brahman!\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[224b:1](sbe15099.htm#fr_694) The Madhyandinas begin with vayam, we, then 1.\nBharadva _g_ iputra, 2. Vatsima _n_ _d_ aviputra, 3. Para _s_ ariputra, 4.\nGargiputra, 5. Para _s_ ari-kau _n_ _d_ iniputra, 6. Gargiputra, 7.\nGargiputra, 8. Ba _d_ eyiputra, 9. Maushikiputra, 10. Harikar _n_ iputra, 11.\nBharadva _g_ iputra, 12. Pai\xe1\xb9\x85giputra, 13. _S_ aunakiputra, 14. Ka _s_ yapi-\nbalakya-ma _th_ ariputra, 15. Kautsiputra, 16. Baudhiputra, 17. _S_\nala\xe1\xb9\x85kayaniputra, 18. Varshaga _n_ iputra, 19. Gautamiputra, 20. \xc3\x82treyiputra,\n21. Gautamiputra, 22. Vatsiputra, 23. Bharadva _g_ iputra, 24. Para _s_\nariputra, 25. Varkaru _n_ iputra; then from No. 20 as in the Ka _n_ va text.\n\nThis stem is called by _S_ a\xe1\xb9\x85kara, Samastaprava _k_ anava _m_ _s_ a _h_ , and\n\xc3\x82nandagiri adds, purvau va _m_ _s_ au purushavi _s_ eshitau, t _ri_ tiyas tu\nstriviseshita _h_ , stripradha _n_ yat. Dvivedaga\xe1\xb9\x85ga writes, putramanthakarma\n_n_ a _h_ strisa _m_ skararthatvenoktatvat tatsannidhanad aya _m_ va _m_ sa\n_h_ stripradhanyeno _k_ yate.\n\n[225:1](sbe15099.htm#fr_695) M. has only one.\n\n[225:2](sbe15099.htm#fr_696) M. inverts 23 and 24.\n\n[225:3](sbe15099.htm#fr_697) Deest in M.\n\n[226:1](sbe15099.htm#fr_698) Vaidabh _ri_ tiputra, M.\n\n[226:2](sbe15099.htm#fr_699) Bhalukiputra, M.\n\n[226:3](sbe15099.htm#fr_700) Kar _s_ akeyiputra after 35 in M.\n\n[226:4](sbe15099.htm#fr_701) They are called _s_ uklani, white or pure,\nbecause they are not mixed with Brahma _n_ as, avyami _s_ ra _n_ i brahma\xe1\xb9\x85ena\n(doshair asa\xe1\xb9\x85kir _n_ ani, paurusheyatvadoshadvarabhavad ityartha _h_ ). Or\nthey are ayatayamani, unimpaired. \xc3\x82nandagiri adds, Pra _g_ apatim arabhya Sa\n_\xc3\xb1_ _g_ iviputraparyanta _m_ (No. 36) Va _g_ asaneyi _s_ akhasu sarvasv eko va\n_m_ sa ityaha samanam iti. Dvivedaga\xe1\xb9\x85ga says: Va _g_ isakhava _k_ _kh_ innana\n_m_ p. 227 ya _g_ usha _m_ Surye _n_ opadish _t_ atva _m_ Ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_ avalkyena\npraptatvam _k_ a pura _n_ eshu prasiddham.\n\n[227:1](sbe15099.htm#fr_702) This last paragraph is wanting in the Madhyandina\ntext, but a very similar paragraph occurs in _S_ atapatha-brahma _n_ a X, 6,\n5, 9, where, however, Vatsya comes before Sandilya.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: Adhyaya I](sbe15100.htm)\n\n'